```rust
use actix_web::{response, App, HttpServer};
async fn hello() -> impl Responder {
    response::from_str("Hello")
}
#[actix_web::main]
async fn main() -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    println!("starting server");
    App::new().service(hello()).run().await
}
```
It compiles? Actually I got `\'Response' object has no member from_str`.

You can use the built‑in numeric extractor or a custom one. Example with a path that parses to i32:
```rust
use actix_web::{App, HttpServer};
async fn hello(path: Path<i32>) -> impl Responder {
    format!("Hello from {}", path)
}
#[actix_web::main]
async fn main() -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    App::new().service(hello()).run().await
}
```
Alternatively, read the string and parse it yourself if you need more control.
